item.title: CVE-2023-27927|2024-08-02T12:23:30.295Z -- sauter -- ey-as525f001%20with%20moduweb
item.description: An authenticated malicious user could acquire the simple mail transfer protocol (SMTP) Password in cleartext format, despite it being protected and hidden behind asterisks. The attacker could then perform further attacks using the SMTP credentials.

item.title: CVE-2023-22300|2024-08-02T10:07:06.208Z -- sauter -- ey-as525f001%20with%20moduweb
item.description: An unauthenticated remote attacker could force all authenticated users, such as administrative users, to perform unauthorized actions by viewing the logs. This action would also grant the attacker privilege escalation.
